\documentclass{article}
\title{Chicken Adobo}
\author{Jordan Bethune}
\usepackage{fullpage}
\begin{document}
\maketitle
\section{Description: Chicken adobo is a delicious pacific island dish that includes the slow cooking of chicken mixed with vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, and onions. The chicken adobo is then served over a bed of rice. }
\section{Ingredients:}
\begin{itemize}
\item 2 tablespoons of olive oil 
\item 2 pounds of chicken, cut up
\item 1 large white onion, sliced 
\item 2 tablespoons minced garlic
\item 1/3 cup of white vinegar 
\item 1 tablespoon of garlic powder 
\item 2/3 cup of low sodium soy sauce 
\item 1 tablespoon of black pepper 
\end{itemize}
\section{Steps:}
\begin{enumerate}
\item Heat olive oil in a large, deep skillet over medium-high heat. 
\item Add the chicken and cook it, then remove from skillet. 
\item In the same skillet stir in the garlic and onion, cook until soften and brown. Roughly 6 minutes. 
\item Pour in vinegar and soy sauce, and season with garlic powder and black pepper. 
\item Add the cooked chicken and increase the heat to high and bring to a boil. 
\item Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until the chicken is tender and cooked all the way through. Roughly 35-40 minutes. 
\item Serve over a bed of rice. Enjoy!
\end{enumerate}
\end{document}
